VCE Assessment tasks (SACs/SATs) are presented as a percentage.

VCE Outcomes

VCE Outcomes are reported using S, N or NA. S denotes ‘satisfactory completion’ of the Unit. N denotes that the Unit has ‘not

been satisfactorily completed’. NA may be given if results have not been assessed due to circumstances beyond the control of

the student.

BIOLOGY UNITS 1 & 2

Catherine AING

Teacher: Ms Charis OOI

Viewbank College - 2023 - Semester One

In this unit students examined the cell as the structural and functional unit of life, from the single celled to the multicellular organism, including the

requirements for sustaining cellular processes. Students focused on cell growth, replacement and death and the role of stem cells in differentiation,

specialisation and renewal of cells. They explored how systems function through cell specialisation in vascular plants and animals, and considered

the role that homeostatic mechanisms play in maintaining an animal’s internal environment.

Victorian Certificate of Education (VCE) Outcomes Overall Result NA

Outcome 1: Explain and compare cellular structure and function and analyse the cell cycle and cell growth, death, and differentiation. S

Outcome 2: Explain and compare how cells are specialised and organised in plants and animals and analyse how specific systems in plants

and animals are regulated. NA

Outcome 3: Adapt or design and then conduct a scientific investigation related to function and/or regulation of cells or systems, and draw a

conclusion based on evidence from generated primary data.

S

Assessment Tasks

Outcome 1: Students undertake investigations and tasks relating to the structure and function of cellular structures. 43%

Outcome 2: Students undertake investigations and tasks relating to the relationships between the features and regulation of systems in

organisms NA

Outcome 3: Students design and conduct a scientific investigation related to the function of plants. 68%

LITERATURE UNITS 1 & 2

Catherine AING

Teacher: Mrs Stavroula MOUZAKIS

Viewbank College - 2023 - Semester One

The focus of this unit is on the reading of a range of texts, particularly narrative and imaginative texts, in order to comprehend, appreciate and

analyse the ways in which texts are constructed and interpreted. Students will develop confidence in creating written, oral and multimodal texts. The

set texts will be chosen by the College for the achievement of outcomes.

Victorian Certificate of Education (VCE) Outcomes Overall Result S

Outcome 1: On completion of this unit the student should be able to respond to a range of texts through close analysis. S

Outcome 2: On completion of this unit the student should be able to explore conventions common to a selected movement or genre, and

engage with the ideas, concerns and representations from at least one complete text alongside multiple samples of other texts considered

characteristic of the selected movement or genre.

S

Assessment Tasks

Outcome 1: Reading practices 83%

Outcome 2: Exploration of literary movements and genres 79%

MATHS METHODS UNITS 1 & 2

Catherine AING

Teacher: Mr Long TRAN

Viewbank College - 2023 - Semester One

In this unit students covered the graphical representation of functions and the key features of graphs of linear, quadratic, cubic, hyperbolic and

power functions. Students applied these functions to a range of contexts with a focus on technology use and interpretation of results. Formal

function notation was emphasised along with correct use of terminology. Students explored the behaviour of functions under transformations in the

plane and used parameters to investigate the features of families of functions.

Each assessment task undertaken in this unit encompass two or more VCE outcomes.

Victorian Certificate of Education (VCE) Outcomes Overall Result NA

Outcome 1: define and explain key concepts and apply a range of related mathematical routines and procedures. NA

Outcome 2: select and apply mathematical facts, concepts, models and techniques to investigate and analyse extended application problems

in a range of contexts. NA

Outcome 3: select and use numerical, graphical, symbolic and statistical functionalities of technology to develop mathematical ideas, produce

results and carry out analysis.

S

Functions and Relations SAC 9%

Polynomials and Transformations Investigation SAC 30%

PSYCHOLOGY UNITS 1 & 2

Catherine AING

Teacher: Miss Chloe TIMMS

Viewbank College - 2023 - Semester One

Human development involves changes in thoughts, feelings and behaviors. In this unit, students investigated the structure and functioning of the

human brain and the role it plays in mental processes and behaviour and explored brain plasticity and the influence that brain damage may have on

a person’s psychological functioning. They considered the complex nature of psychological development, including situations where psychological

development may not occur as expected. Students examined the contribution that classical and contemporary knowledge from Western and non-

Western societies, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, has made to an understanding of psychological development and to the

development of psychological models and theories used to predict and explain the development of thoughts, emotions and behaviours.

Victorian Certificate of Education (VCE) Outcomes Overall Result NA

Outcome 1: Discuss the complexity of psychological development over the life span and evaluate ways of understanding and representing

psychological development.

S

Outcome 2: Analyse the role of the brain in mental processes and behaviour and evaluate how brain plasticity and brain injury can change

biopsychosocial functioning.

S

Outcome 3: Identify, analyse and evaluate the evidence available to answer a research question relating to contemporary psychology. NA

Assessment Tasks

Outcome 1: Case studies looking at the complexity of psychological development. 81%

Outcome 2: Media Analysis of media relating to brain structures and function. 66%

Outcome 3: Student directed research investigation. NA
